{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require schools to have a separate behaviour policy for SEND students",
        "additional_details": "We believe SEND students are not being given adequate consideration with regards to their behaviour in mainstream schools.\r\n \r\nWe are concerned that many SEND students are not getting their right to a fair education, on part because of behaviour policies in mainstream schools, which we believe often don't recognise their individual circumstances.\r\n",
        "background": "I think behaviour policies in mainstream schools are primarily written for neuro-typical students, which can result in SEND students struggling to access the curriculum and be properly understood and supported.",
